use<br />that will just mean that bots will randomly fail if they set that<br />option, and if we make it harder to set developers won't have it set<br />anyway, and it doesn't help much.<br /><br />End result: using -Werror works wonderfully in controlled<br />environments. Not so wonderfully in the general random mess.<br /><br />That said, I've been so aggressive against accepting new warnings that<br />I've considered this unconditionally anyway, and then dealing with<br />compiler version fallout by just disabling certain compilers and/or<br />certain options.<br /><br />But it would almost certainly be pretty painful.<br /><br />                     Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
